00:31:44.741 --> 00:31:50.590
that's managed out there.
It's impossible to manage at our scales, but

00:31:50.590 --> 00:31:55.120
at the personal scale, when you have a million
followers, how do you crowd source in meaningful

00:31:55.120 --> 00:31:58.440
ways?
You mention that you got a lot of value from

00:31:58.440 --> 00:31:59.610
that.
How do you manage that, I guess?

00:31:59.610 --> 00:32:03.780
Padmasree Warrior: Yeah. It's a great question.
You know, in the beginning, when I first started,

00:32:03.780 --> 00:32:08.730
I was one of the earlier adopters of Twitter.
I think, when I started, there were very few

00:32:08.730 --> 00:32:11.660
people on Twitter.
And at the time, I felt like I could say anything

00:32:11.660 --> 00:32:15.080
I wanted to, because nobody was really reading
it.

00:32:15.080 --> 00:32:18.020
And then, all of a sudden, you find out that
everybody's reading it, right?

00:32:18.020 --> 00:32:21.520
I recognize that Wall Street Journal is following
me, and everybody else is following me.

00:32:21.520 --> 00:32:26.680
So now, you know, then you realize, "Oops.
Maybe I have to be more careful what I say.”

00:32:26.680 --> 00:32:31.740
But actually what I've found to be most useful
for me is, when I am thinking about a concept,

00:32:31.740 --> 00:32:35.320
for example, collaboration.
